At the same time, Metcash loses market share in the eastern Länder mainly to Ald and Coles, although a recent Roy Morgan study found that IGA customers were among the most loyal.
Morgan Stanley believes Metcash’s food and food sales will fall by 3.8 percent in 2016; by 4.1 percent in 2017 and by 2.1 percent in 2018, with its market share falling from 14 percent in 2015 to 10.3% in 2020.
